<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 27 at 7:42PM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A SHOWER WILL AFFECT
ROCKINGHAM AND SOUTH CENTRAL HENRY COUNTIES...
At 740 PM EST, a band of heavy rainfall was located over Wentworth,
moving northeast at 40 mph. Rainfall rates of 1 to locally 2 inches
per hour are falling with this band.
Locations impacted include...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
Stoneville...
and Mayfield.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
